1 Sec. 9. “Fabric treatment” means a product applied to fabric
2 to give the fabric one or more characteristics, including, without
3 limitation, stain resistance or water resistance. The term does not
4 include hydrofluoroolefins used as propellants in fabric
5 treatments.
6 Sec. 10. “Food packaging” means a package or packaging
7 component that is used in direct contact with food and is
8 composed, in substantial part, of paper, paperboard or other
9 materials originally derived from plant fibers.
10 Sec. 11. 1. “Intentionally added perfluoroalkyl and
11 polyfluoroalkyl substances” means perfluoroalkyl and
12 polyfluoroalkyl substances that a manufacturer has intentionally
13 added to a product and that have a functional or technical effect
14 on the product. The term includes, without limitation,
15 perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances that are intentional
16 breakdown products of an added chemical that also have a
17 functional or technical effect on the product.
18 2. The term does not include the use of recycled materials
19 which may contain perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances
20 due to the use of perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances in
21 the original product.
22 Sec. 11.5. 1. “Juvenile product” means a product designed
23 by a manufacturer for use by an infant or child less than 12 years
24 of age, including, without limitation, a bassinet, child restraint
25 system for use in motor vehicles, changing pad, toddler mattress,
26 crib mattress or other sleep product for infants, high chair, infant
27 carrier, infant seat, polyurethane foam mat, pad or pillow, nap cot,
28 play mat, playpen or stroller.
29 2. The term does not include:
30 (a) Electronic products, including, without limitation, any
31 personal computer and any associated equipment, audio and video
32 equipment, calculator, wireless phone, gaming console, handheld
33 device incorporating a video screen or any associated peripheral
34 device such as a mouse, keyboard, power supply unit or power
35 cord;
36 (b) An internal component of a juvenile product that is not
37 designed or intended to come into direct contact with the skin or
38 mouth of a child as a result of the reasonably foreseeable use of
39 the product;
40 (c) An adult mattress; or
41 (d) An off-highway vehicle, as defined in NRS 490.060,
42 designed for use by a child, a replacement part for such an off-
43 highway vehicle and any protective clothing or equipment
44 intended for use by a child while operating such an off-highway
45 vehicle.
