18 Sec. 21. 1. A manufacturer shall not sell, offer for sale,
19 distribute for sale or distribute for use in this State any of the
20 following types of products if the product contains intentionally
21 added perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances:
22 (a) Carpets or rugs;
23 (b) Fabric treatments;
24 (c) Food packaging;
25 (d) Juvenile products;
26 (e) Cosmetics;
27 (f) Indoor textile furnishings; or
28 (g) Indoor upholstered furniture.
29 2. A manufacturer of the products described in subsection 1
30 may include on the product label a sticker suitable to the size of
31 the product label stating “NO PFAS” to inform the consumer that
32 the product does not contain intentionally added perfluoroalkyl
33 and polyfluoroalkyl substances.
34 3. The provisions of this section do not apply to:
35 (a) A product which contains perfluoroalkyl and
36 polyfluoroalkyl substances due to the use of recycled materials
37 containing perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances in the
38 original product;
39 (b) A carpet or rug that was manufactured or imported before
40 October 1, 2024; or
41 (c) Any other textile product, other than a carpet or rug, that
42 was manufactured or imported before October 1, 2024.
43 Sec. 22. 1. A manufacturer of cookware sold in this State
44 that contains intentionally added perfluoroalkyl and
45 polyfluoroalkyl substances in the handle of the product or in any
